 Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":49,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":84,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705190,"age":115,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When William of Culmington de Burley II was born in 1175, in Shropshire, England, his father, William de Burley I, was 25 and his mother, de Hugley, was 20. He had at least 2 sons with Edeline de Jay. He died in England."},"et":{"1175–":"1175–Surnud","1170–1202":"1170–1202","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1178–Male":"1178–Surnud","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","1200–1283":"1200–1283","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1155–Female":"1155–Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1202":"1202","1200":"1200","1178":"1178","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","1283":"1283","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","1290":"1290","Burley, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1175–":"1175–Kuollut","1170–1202":"1170–1202","1175–Male":"